The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Sept. 2: Leading steel makers SAIL and Tata Steel today hiked the prices of some of their products by up to Rs 1,500 a tonne on improvement in demand, while their peers are considering similar options. We have raised prices of our flat products (used for car manufacturing) by Rs 1,500 a tonne in line with the rising international prices, a SAIL spokesperson said.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 2: IL amp;FS, the new promoter of Maytas Infra, today made an offer to buy an additional 20 per cent stake in the firm at Rs 112.80 a share. IL amp;FS said its open offer would begin on October 24 and close on November 12, 2009.                             
	 Mumbai, Sept. 2: MCX-SX, jointly promoted by Financial Technologies (India) Ltd and MCX, the commodity bourse, today got a relief when Sebi gave a one-year extension till September 15, 2010 to complete its divestment.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 2: Mobile service provider Tata Teleservices today launched the countrys first 3G-enabled netbook in a collaboration with CDMA chip maker Qualcomm.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 2: Hospitality major Accor will make equity investment of Rs 636 crore in India for setting up 50 hotels over the next 2-3 years.                                                                                                                           
